{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 200°C and line a baking tray with baking paper.","Place sweet potatoes on baking tray, drizzle with 1-2 Tbsp olive oil and season with salt and pepper, to taste. Roast for 25-30 minutes (200°C) until browned and soft. Meanwhile, continue with recipe.","Place Parmesan in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place garlic, onions, 15 g sage leaves and 30 g oil in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add rice and wine then, without measuring cup, sauté <nobr>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add water, vegetable stock, ½ tsp salt and 2 pinches pepper then scrape base of mixing bowl well with spatula to loosen rice. Place simmering basket instead of measuring cup on mixing bowl lid and cook <nobr>12-13 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr> until rice is cooked.","Add butter, blue cheese, pecans, reserved grated Parmesan and half roasted sweet potatoes. Stir gently with spatula to combine. Leave risotto to rest in mixing bowl for 2 minutes then divide between serving plates and serve immediately, topped with remaining roasted sweet potatoes and remaining 1-2 sprigs sage leaves."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["800 g sweet potatoes, skin on, diced (2 cm)","60 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)","2 garlic cloves","100 g onions, quartered","15 g fresh sage leaves, plus 1-2 sprigs leaves only for garnishing","30 g olive oil, plus 1-2 Tbsp for drizzling","320 g risotto rice (e.g. carnaroli, Arborio)","60 g dry white wine","820 g water, boiling","1 vegetable stock cube (for 0.5 l), crumbled","½ tsp fine sea salt, plus extra to taste","2 pinches ground black pepper, plus extra to taste","20 g unsalted butter, diced","100 g blue cheese, crumbled","80 g pecan nuts, roughly chopped"]}],"id":"r315707","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-